rewling, Gundela Hachmann, Andrew Wright Hurley, Christina Kraenzle, Magda Tarnawaska Senel, Monika Shafi, Sunka Simon. Karin Baumgartner is Professor of German at the University of Utah. Monika Shafi is Elias Ahuja Professor of German at the University of Delaware.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGerman prose literaturexHistory and criticismy21st century. 0aTourism in literature. 0aTravel in literature. 0aTravelers' writings, GermanxHistory and criticism. 4aGerman Literature. 4aTravel. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aEuropean project.  aGerman literature.  aGerman.  aTwenty-First-Century Travel Writing.  acontemporary travel narratives.  acrisis.  acultural disintegration.  aidentity.  amass migration.  atravelogues.1 aBaumgartner, Karin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaumgartner, Karin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBenbow, Heather Merle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiendarra, Anke S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlair, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColeman, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCormican, Muriel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaffner, Carola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerhardt, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrewling, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHachmann, Gundela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHurley, Andrew Wright, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKraenzle, Christina, ec